    <h2 class="title is-2">Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>Schurer Solutions Incorporated D/B/A upSpace (“upSpace”, ”We”) is committed to protecting your privacy. We make the website https://upspace.ca (the “Website”) available together with our services as described in our Terms of Use. This Privacy
      Policy describes how we collect, store, use and distribute information about our users through the Website.</p>
    <p>This Privacy Policy was last modified on: June 9, 2018.</p>
    <p>If you do not agree to any part of this Privacy Policy, then we cannot provide the Services to you, and you should stop accessing the Services and deactivate your account.</p>
    <p>Any definition of a term that does not appear in this Privacy Policy (such as “Listing”, “Space”, “Content”, “Services” etc.) shall be given its definition as outlined in our Terms of Service (http://www.upSpace.ca/terms).</p>

    <p class="subtitle is-3 mt-5">What personal information do we collect from users directly and how do we use it?</p>
    <p>You can register for a upSpace account using either your account for a social networking service (“SNS”) we support (e.g. Facebook) or directly through the Site using your email address.</p>
    <p>If registering using your SNS account, you allow upSpace to access your SNS account information for the purposes of creating a upSpace account and collect the following information: first and last name, email, and, if provided on your SNS account,
      phone number.</p>
    <p>If registering using your email address, we require: (i) your email address, and (ii) first and last name, and (iii) your password. You will not receive marketing communications unless you consent on registration.</p>
    <p>We do not collect information from you when you request information from upSpace or about the Services. You can comment on our blog postings using Facebook’s commenting platform, but we do not collect any information from you.</p>
    <p>We use the information you provide at registration to communicate with you regarding and to administer the Services, including, without limitation, listing or booking a space, allowing users to communicate with other users, and reviewing a Space
      or Lister. Except the information a Lister provides when creating a Listing (see below), upSpace will not disclose any of the contact information (including your first and last name) to other users.</p>

    <p class="subtitle is-3 mt-5">What information do we collect about your Space?</p>
    <p>When a Lister lists a Space, you are required to specify:</p>
    <p>• space type (e.g. yoga studio, dance studio, music recording studio, etc.),</p>
    <p>• the name of the Space,</p>
    <p>• a description of the Space,</p>
    <p>• any rules you have about the Space,</p>
    <p>• amenities and features of the Space,</p>
    <p>• the location,</p>
    <p>• the Space Booking Fee,</p>
    <p>• whether the Space is available on an hourly or daily basis,</p>
    <p>• your cancellation policy, and</p>
    <p>You also have the ability to upload photos and videos of your Space for the Listing, based on your chosen Subscription Plan.</p>
    <p>This information will be used to create the Listing and will be provided to potential Renters. When a Listing is viewed by the public, users will be able see a Lister’s Username nd a brief summary about the Lister which is created by the Lister
      and users.</p>

    <p class="subtitle is-3 mt-5">What information do we automatically collect from users and how do we use it?</p>
    <p>upSpace gathers information from your computer, mobile or web-enabled devices when you visit our Sites or use our Application. We collect your IP address, the date and time you access our websites, the browser you are using, the Internet address
      of the website from which you linked directly to our website, the operating system you are using, the sections of the website you visit, the website pages read and images viewed, and the content you download from the website. This information is used
      for website and system administration purposes and to improve the websites. All of this information remains non-personally identifiable , except when you initiate a chat for help with our support team using our chat tool, where we may link this
      information so that our support team is able to assist you in providing customer support. In other words, except as described above, we do not attempt to link your IP address or any other information listed above with information that would identify
      you.</p>
    <p>Location Information</p>
    <p>When you use a mobile or other web-enabled device, we may also collect location based information based on your device’s GPS or other location tracking functionality. If you access the Services through a mobile or other web-enabled device and you do
    not want your device to provide us with location-tracking information, you can disable the GPS or other location-tracking functions on your device.</p>
    <p>Google Analytics</p>
    <p>The Sites also use Google Analytics, a web analytics tool provided by Google, Inc. (“Google”) and/or other tracking tools that help website owners understand how visitors engage with their website. We can view a variety of reports about how users
