    <p class="subtitle is-3 mt-5">Do the upSpace Sites and Application use cookies?</p>
    <p>When you view our Sites, we might store some information on your computer or mobile or other web-enabled device in the form of a “cookie” or similar file. We may also allow our business partners to use their cookies on the Sites. For example, as
      discussed above, we use Google Analytics for web analytics, and so Google may also set cookies on your device. There are two types of cookies used on the Platform, namely “persistent cookies” and “session cookies”. Session cookies will normally
      expire when you close your browser, while persistent cookies will remain on your device after you close your browser, and can be used again the next time you access the Services.
    </p>
    <p>Cookies are used to customize your user interface, speed up the navigation process, and make your website experience more efficient. You may choose to decline cookies, if your browser permits, but doing so may affect your use of the website and
      your ability to access certain features of the website.</p>

